nodes.bodyText:
I think the concern here is that in the absence of reset calls the cost of acquiring a read lock will still be incurred despite the high probability of a cache hit.
@xnull to address this issue, the lock doesn't have to be moved to StreamLogFiles, it can be moved to LogUnitServerCache::handleRetrieval that way the cost of the lock will only be incurred on a cache miss, which should have a low probability (since we usually see cache hit rates of ~90%).
@WenbinZhu I think that there are other bottlenecks in the stack that we would hit before this being a problem. You can get some sense of read lock latency without contention here https://mechanical-sympathy.blogspot.com/2013/08/lock-based-vs-lock-free-concurrent.html

